3. ROOT CAUSE ANALYSIS
================================================================================

The previous session (see 2026-04-26-infra-debug-guardrails.log) applied the
fix: launch template v10 with `systemctl stop ecs` before S3 sync and
`systemctl start ecs` after. The template source was correct. But the fix
never reached workers.

Discovery chain:

  a) Decoded UserData from nf-reads-profiler-worker v10 (the source template):
     - Has the stop guard — correct
     - BUT the UserData was duplicated: two identical MIME multipart documents
       concatenated together (two systemctl stop/start pairs)

  b) Checked the Batch-managed launch templates (Batch-lt-*-rev-2):
     - These are what workers ACTUALLY boot with
     - Batch snapshots the source template UserData when the CE is created
     - ALL four managed templates had systemctl stop count: 0
     - They were still using the OLD UserData from v9 (no stop guard)

  c) Checked v9 of nf-reads-profiler-worker:
     - No `systemctl stop ecs` at top
     - Used `systemctl restart ecs` at the end (not stop-before/start-after)
     - This was the version the Batch-managed templates had baked in

  Root cause: AWS Batch does NOT dynamically re-read the source launch
  template when CEs reference $Latest. It snapshots the UserData at CE
  creation/update time. Updating the source template to v10 with the fix
  had no effect because the CEs were never told to re-snapshot.

================================================================================
4. FIX APPLIED
================================================================================

  Step 1: Attempted CloudFormation deploy — no template changes, so no-op.

  Step 2: Disabled both CEs:
    SpotComputeEnvironment-Eyi8eJp5FEi4DwVk    → DISABLED
    OnDemandComputeEnvironme-BlIl26JdB3ef8RMS   → DISABLED

  Step 3: Simple disable/re-enable did NOT regenerate managed templates.
    Batch-lt-* names stayed at rev-2 with the same stale UserData.

  Step 4: Explicitly updated both CEs with launch template + updateToLatestImageVersion:
    aws batch update-compute-environment \
      --compute-environment <CE> \
      --compute-resources '{"launchTemplate":{"launchTemplateId":"lt-0d9193dd0f66d68ee","version":"$Latest"},"updateToLatestImageVersion":true}' \
      --region us-east-2

  Step 5: This triggered Batch to create new managed templates (rev-3):
    Batch-lt-1c8bf6c4-...-rev-3   systemctl stop ecs count: 1 ✓
    Batch-lt-e6beaf02-...-rev-3   systemctl stop ecs count: 1 ✓
    No duplication — 1 stop, 1 start, 3 MIME parts (our script + Batch ECS config)

